## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Scope

This ticket delivers three infrastructure improvements to the Code Intelligence indexing pipeline:

1. **Full-body Embedding** — Embed entire function/method bodies (not just signatures) for semantic search that understands implementation details
2. **Persistent Graph** — Store the code graph in SQLite/RocksDB for instant startup (< 500ms) without re-parsing on every restart
3. **.codeintelignore** — Per-folder exclusion file (like .gitignore) allowing users to exclude directories/files from indexing

These are foundational infrastructure changes that improve quality (embedding), performance (persistence), and usability (ignore).

### 1.2 Out of Scope

* Changing the embedding model itself (model selection is separate)
* Distributed/multi-workspace graph federation
* Real-time file watching (inotify/fswatch) — uses polling/on-demand
* Graph visualization UI
* Cloud-based persistent storage (local only)

### 1.3 Preliminary Requirements

* KSA-145: Tree-sitter Core Integration (AST parsing for body extraction)
* KSA-153: Graph Storage Engine (base graph infrastructure)
* KSA-39: Embedding Engine (current signature-only embedding)
* Existing SQLite + sqlite-vec infrastructure

## 2. Business Requirements

### 2.1 High Level Process Map

Currently, the Code Intelligence system: - Embeds only function signatures (name + params + return type) — misses implementation semantics - Re-indexes from scratch on every server restart — slow startup for large projects - Has no per-folder exclusion — users cannot exclude generated code, vendor dirs, etc.

This ticket addresses all three gaps to bring infrastructure parity with CodeGraph.

### 2.2 List of User Stories / Use Cases

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| # | Story / Use Case | Priority | Source Ticket |
| 1 | As a developer, I want semantic search to understand function bodies so that I can find implementations by what they do | MUST HAVE | KSA-169 |
| 2 | As a developer, I want instant startup (< 500ms) so that the server is ready immediately | MUST HAVE | KSA-169 |
| 3 | As a developer, I want to exclude folders via .codeintelignore so that generated/vendor code doesn’t pollute results | MUST HAVE | KSA-169 |
| 4 | As a developer, I want incremental graph updates so that only changed files are re-processed | SHOULD HAVE | KSA-169 |
| 5 | As a developer, I want improved search relevance for “how does X work” queries | SHOULD HAVE | KSA-169 |

### 2.3 Details of User Stories

#### Business Flow

**Step 1:** Server starts → loads persistent graph from disk (< 500ms)

**Step 2:** Server checks file modification times against stored hashes

**Step 3:** Only modified files are re-parsed and re-embedded (incremental update)

**Step 4:** For new/modified files, extract full function bodies via tree-sitter AST

**Step 5:** Chunk large bodies (> 512 tokens) into overlapping segments

**Step 6:** Generate embeddings for each chunk, store in vector index

**Step 7:** Update graph edges (calls, imports, inheritance) for modified files

**Step 8:** Server ready for queries — semantic search uses full-body embeddings

**Step 9:** .codeintelignore rules applied at scan time — excluded files never parsed

#### STORY 1: Full-body Embedding

As a developer, I want semantic search to understand function bodies so that I can find implementations by what they do, not just their names.

**Requirement Details:**

1. Extract complete function/method bodies from AST (tree-sitter)
2. For bodies <= 512 tokens: embed as single vector
3. For bodies > 512 tokens: chunk with 128-token overlap, embed each chunk
4. Store body embeddings alongside signature embeddings (dual-vector approach)
5. Semantic search queries match against both signature AND body embeddings
6. Ranking: combine signature similarity (weight 0.3) + body similarity (weight 0.7)

**Chunking Strategy:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Body Size | Strategy | Chunks |
| <= 512 tokens | Single embedding | 1 |
| 513-1024 tokens | 2 chunks, 128 overlap | 2 |
| 1025-2048 tokens | 4 chunks, 128 overlap | 4 |
| > 2048 tokens | Sliding window 512/128 | N |

**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. All function bodies extracted and embedded (not just signatures)
2. Semantic search for “sort array using quicksort” finds quicksort implementations even if function is named partition\_sort
3. Search relevance improves >= 30% on benchmark queries (body-relevant queries)
4. Embedding storage size increase < 5x compared to signature-only
5. Indexing time increase < 2x compared to signature-only

#### STORY 2: Persistent Graph (Instant Startup)

As a developer, I want instant startup (< 500ms) so that the code intelligence server is ready immediately.

**Requirement Details:**

1. Serialize full code graph (nodes + edges + metadata) to disk on shutdown/checkpoint
2. On startup, load graph from disk — no re-parsing needed
3. Storage format: SQLite WAL (leveraging existing infrastructure)
4. Graph includes: symbol nodes, relationship edges, file metadata, content hashes
5. Incremental update: compare file hashes, only re-process changed files
6. Checkpoint strategy: save every 5 minutes during active indexing, save on graceful shutdown

**Performance Targets:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Metric | Target | Current |
| Cold start (first index) | Same as current | ~60 files/sec |
| Warm start (persistent) | < 500ms | N/A (re-indexes) |
| Incremental update (10 files changed) | < 2s | Full re-index |
| Graph load (10K symbols) | < 300ms | N/A |
| Graph load (100K symbols) | < 1s | N/A |

**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. Server starts in < 500ms for previously-indexed project (up to 50K symbols)
2. No data loss on crash (WAL journaling)
3. Incremental update processes only changed files
4. Graph version tracking prevents stale data
5. Storage size < 500MB for 100K-symbol project

#### STORY 3: .codeintelignore Support

As a developer, I want to exclude folders from indexing via .codeintelignore so that generated/vendor code doesn’t pollute results.

**Requirement Details:**

1. File name: .codeintelignore (placed in any directory)
2. Syntax: identical to .gitignore (glob patterns, negation with !, comments with #)
3. Cascading: child directory .codeintelignore overrides parent
4. Default ignores (built-in, always applied):
   * node\_modules/, .git/, build/, dist/, target/
   * \_\_pycache\_\_/, .pytest\_cache/
   * \*.min.js, \*.bundle.js
   * .gradle/, .idea/
5. User can override defaults with negation: !build/ to include build dir
6. Applied at scan time — excluded files never parsed, never embedded, never in graph

**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. .codeintelignore files parsed correctly (gitignore syntax)
2. Excluded files do not appear in search results or graph
3. Cascading rules work (child overrides parent)
4. Default ignores applied even without .codeintelignore file
5. Negation patterns work correctly
6. Performance: ignore check adds < 1ms per file

#### STORY 4: Incremental Graph Updates

As a developer, I want incremental graph updates so that only changed files are re-processed.

**Requirement Details:**

1. On startup, scan file system for changes against stored hashes
2. Compare: mtime + content\_hash (FNV-1a) against stored values
3. Changed files: re-parse AST, update graph nodes/edges, re-embed
4. Deleted files: remove nodes/edges from graph, remove embeddings
5. New files: add to graph, embed
6. Unchanged files: skip entirely

**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. Only changed files are re-processed on startup
2. Deleted files are cleaned from graph and embeddings
3. New files are automatically discovered and indexed
4. Rename detection works (same content, different path)
5. Incremental update for 10 changed files in 10K-file project < 5s

