## 5. Risks and Assumptions

### 5.1 Risks

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |
| Storage size explosion with full-body embeddings | High | Medium | Chunking strategy, compression, configurable max body size |
| Persistent graph corruption on crash | High | Low | WAL journaling, checksum verification |
| Incremental update misses changes (stale graph) | Medium | Low | Content hash verification, periodic full re-index option |
| .codeintelignore parsing edge cases | Low | Medium | Use battle-tested gitignore library |
| Embedding quality varies by function size | Medium | Medium | Chunking with overlap, weighted scoring |

### 5.2 Assumptions

* Tree-sitter AST provides reliable function body boundaries
* SQLite WAL mode handles concurrent read/write safely
* Embedding model handles code bodies reasonably well
* 512-token chunk size is optimal for code embedding quality
* Users will adopt .codeintelignore similar to .gitignore

